> I had a simple question about Camlidl.  I notice that there has not
> been a release since the change to the LGPL and the other license.
> The LICENSE file in Camlidl gives rights to distribute the files
> generated by Camlidl, but no mention is given to the runtime library
> files required.
> What is the intended distribution terms of these files?

The same terms as those of the OCaml system, e.g. Q for the compiler
and LGPL for the runtime library.  The next release of CamlIDL (if I
can find time to work on it!) will be made under those new terms.

- Xavier Leroy


